      "content": "You say \"the rare cases,\" but that's the problem. When those complex issues hit—the ones that actually drive our CSAT scores—the templates are going to fail miserably. It's going to be a mess of angry customers and escalations. Don't you think there's a massive risk in cutting out the reasoning capabilities entirely just to save a few bucks?",
